The domestic and economic lives of women, regardless of their social status and ethnicity, are highly dependent on their spouses. Women’s independence and participation in positive decision making for family purchase and consumption decisions are important factors to ensure stable and resilient living conditions.35 Educational opportunities for women can plays a significant role in opening up financial opportunities in the Nauru workforce and potentially increase income for a household and promote resilience. In the last 10 years, there is over a 60% increase in the increase of women entrepreneurs in Nauru registered with the Nauru Union Bank Limited.36 Female dominated jobs include domestic service, food preparation, retail sales, and supporting occupations such as child care workers, nurses and secret
